Class BaseGraphicsLayer

java.lang.Object
  |

All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable, ElementContainer, GraphicsLayer, Layer, Searchable, Selectable, SelectableLayer
Direct Known Subclasses:
BaseFeatureGraphicsLayer
public class BaseGraphicsLayer
extends BaseLayer
implements GraphicsLayer

A helper class for the GraphicsLayer object. Please note that eventhough the API here allows you to add a com.esri.mo2.map.core.Element object, the implementation here only accepts the com.esri.mo2.map.dpy.Element type of objects since the change was for backward compatibility only.

addElement

public SelectionSet addElement(Element element,
                               int zorder)
Description copied from interface: ElementContainer
Adds a graphic element with immediate z-order value specified. Z-order is a "hint" for where to place the Element in the z-order hierarchy and if <= 0 will be placed at the bottom of the z-order (will be drawn first). If zorder >= size() then the Element will be placed at the top of z-order, i.e. will be drawn last.

Specified by:
addElement in interface ElementContainer
Parameters:
element - the graphic element
zorder - the initial z-order of the Element
Returns:
a SelectionSet identifying the element just added
See Also:
ElementContainer.addElement(Element)
